RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 1 770 Y Dirt CR: 70. Allowance Purse 15000. For Three Year Olds and Upward Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FAST EH was quickest to the turn, turned back a challenge from SS PINEAPPLE, and drove clear. SS PINEAPPLE vied between foes for the early lead, pressed FAST EH into the final turn but lacked the rally needed. J. CRUZ lacked early speed and bid belatedly. TIMBERS MOON vied outside, and flattened out. TRUST ELLA lacked bid. BIG BOSS chased outside and tired. THREE DAY BENDER broke slow and trailed throughout.

CAROSWAY pressed the early pace, was unable to move on with the eventual winner, and faded. BODYMOOR HEATH raced at the back of the pack while four wide, and was outrun.

BLAZING SUN chased inside and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CASHLINGS saved ground from a rail position, set sights on dueling leaders, angled out to the four path and got up just in time. LIL ZAPPER sent for speed crossing over quickly to the rail, took pressure through the far turn inside of GODGUNSNCOUNTRY, dueled determinedly into the stretch, and was narrowly denied. GODGUNSNCOUNTRY lacked a clear path leaving, raced wide through the opening turn, moved up while four wide to challenge the front, was headed into the lane, and was bested after a long hard drive. AGENT C settled inside early, chased leaving the backstretch, and lacked room late. OMEGASSHOOTINGSTAR prompted the pace into the backstretch, and had nothing left in reserve late. SNAP COUNT lagged early and showed a mild interest late. SPOT ON DUDE raced five to six wide through the first turn, gave chase leaving the backstretch, and flattened out. HIGH FLYIN TIGER fanned three wide leaving the front side, and faded gradually along the rail. TRICKY SPEEDSTER was rated well off the pace, and was outrun.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: READYTOTAPNSING fanned four wide leaving the opening turn, contested the lead entering the stretch, and edged away. SAXON SAGA contended the early pace from the rail, responded to outside challengers in the final turn, and was outkicked. WALKTHELINE prompted the early pace between rivals, pressed from the three path in the backstretch, and lacked the rally needed in the drive, just holding on for show. WAR GIANT tracked four wide into the opening turn, gave chased in the far turn, closed gradually, and just missed. BACKSTREET BOBBY raced three wide leaving the first turn, lost position in the backstretch, and finished up evenly. DOC COPE hustled away and dropped back through the backstretch. NORTHERN JEWEL failed to threaten. BON PRIX fractious before the break resulting in a slow start, and trailed throughout. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Board of Stewards conducted an inquiry into the start of the race involving BON PRIX, no change was made as it was determined that BON PRIX did receive a fair start.
